💬 ChatGPT Playground for Beginners: Intro to NLP AI – MOOC Summary
This repository documents my learning journey through the “ChatGPT Playground for Beginners: Intro to NLP AI” course. Designed for beginners, the course introduces the fundamentals of Natural Language Processing (NLP) using interactive tools like ChatGPT to explore real-world language tasks with AI.

📘 Course Overview:
In this course, I explored how AI understands and generates human language, including:

Basics of Natural Language Processing (NLP)

Key concepts: tokens, embeddings, language models

Using ChatGPT for language tasks like summarization, translation, and Q&A

Prompt engineering fundamentals

Ethical AI usage and limitations

🛠️ Skills & Topics Covered:
Natural Language Processing (NLP)

AI-Powered Language Tools

Prompt Engineering Basics

Hands-on AI Exploration for Beginners

📁 Repository Includes:
📄 Simple notes on NLP concepts

🤖 Prompts and use cases explored in ChatGPT Playground

✅ Mini practice activities and exercises

🧠 Summary of key takeaways and examples

🎯 Objective:
To develop a foundational understanding of how AI and NLP work together, and to learn how tools like ChatGPT can assist in real-world language-based tasks—even for non-coders and beginners.

